086    /**
087     *  The implementation of
088     *  {@link Builder}
089     *  for a class.
090     *
091     *  @extauthor  Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
092     *  @thanks Square,Inc.
093     *  @version $Id: RecordSpecImpl.java 936 2021-12-13 16:08:37Z tquadrat $
094     *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
095     *  @version $Id: RecordSpecImpl.java 936 2021-12-13 16:08:37Z tquadrat $
096     *  @since 0.2.0

098     *  @UMLGraph.link
099     */
100    @ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: RecordSpecImpl.java 936 2021-12-13 16:08:37Z tquadrat $" )
101    @API( status = INTERNAL, since = "0.2.0" )
102    public static final class BuilderImpl extends TypeSpecImpl.BuilderImpl
103    {
104            /*--------------*\
105        ====** Constructors **=================================================
106            \*--------------*/
107        /**
108         *  Creates a new {@code BuilderImpl} instance.
109         *
110         *  @param  composer    The reference to the factory that created this
111         *      builder instance.
112         *  @param  name    The name of the type to build.
113         */
114        @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
115        public BuilderImpl( final JavaComposer composer, final CharSequence name )
116        {
117            super( composer, RECORD, Optional.of( requireNotEmptyArgument( name, "name" ).toString() ) );
118        }   //  BuilderImpl()
119
120            /*---------*\
121        ====** Methods **======================================================
122            \*---------*/
123        /**
124         *  {@inheritDoc}
125         */
126        @SuppressWarnings( "CastToConcreteClass" )
127        @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
128        @Override
129        public final BuilderImpl addAttribute( final FieldSpec fieldSpec, final boolean readOnly )
130        {
131            final var fieldSpecImpl = (FieldSpecImpl) requireValidNonNullArgument( fieldSpec, "fieldSpec", v -> v.hasModifier( PRIVATE ), $ -> format( "Field %s needs to be private", fieldSpec.name() ) );
132            addField( fieldSpecImpl );
133
134            final var fieldName = fieldSpecImpl.name();
135            final var propertyName = decapitalize( fieldName.startsWith( "m_" ) ? fieldName.substring( 2 )  : fieldName );
136
137            final Set<Modifier> modifiers = EnumSet.of( PUBLIC, FINAL );
138            if( fieldSpec.hasModifier( STATIC ) ) modifiers.add( STATIC );
139
140            final var accessor = getFactory().methodBuilder( propertyName )
141                .addModifiers( modifiers )
142                .returns( fieldSpecImpl.type() )
143                .addStatement( "return $N", fieldSpecImpl )
144                .build();
145            addMethod( accessor );
146
147            if( !(readOnly || fieldSpecImpl.hasModifier( FINAL )) )
148            {
149                final var param = getFactory().parameterBuilder( fieldSpecImpl.type(), "value", FINAL )
150                    .build();
151                final var setter = getFactory().methodBuilder( propertyName )
152                    .addModifiers( modifiers )
153                    .addParameter( param )
154                    .returns( VOID_PRIMITIVE )
155                    .addStatement( "$N = $N", fieldSpecImpl, param )
156                    .build();
157                addMethod( setter );
158            }
159
160            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
161            return this;
162        }   //  addAttribute()
163
164        /**
165         *  {@inheritDoc}
166         */
167        @Override
168        @SuppressWarnings( "CastToConcreteClass" )
169        public TypeSpecImpl.BuilderImpl addField( final FieldSpec fieldSpec )
170        {
171            final var validation = (Predicate<FieldSpec>) f ->
172            {
173                if( f.hasModifier( STATIC ) )
174                {
175                    return !f.hasModifier( PROTECTED );
176                }
177                else
178                {
179                    return f.hasModifier( PRIVATE ) && !f.hasModifier( FINAL );
180                }
181            };
182            super.addField( requireValidNonNullArgument( fieldSpec, "fieldSpec", validation, $ -> "Invalid modifiers for record field" ) );
183
184            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
185            return this;
186        }   //  addField()
187
188        /**
189         *  {@inheritDoc}
190         */
191        @Override
192        @SuppressWarnings( "CastToConcreteClass" )
193        public final BuilderImpl addMethod( final MethodSpec methodSpec )
194        {
195            final var methodSpecImpl = (MethodSpecImpl) requireNonNullArgument( methodSpec, "methodSpec" );
196            checkState( methodSpecImpl.defaultValue().isEmpty(), () -> new IllegalStateException( format( "%s %s.%s cannot have a default value", RECORD, getName().orElse( NAME_ANONYMOUS_TYPE ), methodSpecImpl.name() ) ) );
197            checkState( !methodSpecImpl.hasModifier( DEFAULT ), () -> new IllegalStateException( format( "%s %s.%s cannot be default", RECORD, getName().orElse( NAME_ANONYMOUS_TYPE ), methodSpecImpl.name() ) ) );
198
199            final var methodSpecs = getMethodSpecs();
200            if( composer().addDebugOutput() )
201            {
202                final var builder = methodSpecImpl.toBuilder( false );
203                createDebugOutput( true ).ifPresent( debug -> builder.addJavadoc( "\n$L\n", debug.asLiteral() ) );
204                methodSpecs.add( builder.build() );
205            }
206            else
207            {
208                methodSpecs.add( methodSpecImpl );
209            }
210
211            final var maxMethods = composer().getMaxMethods();
212            if( (maxMethods > 0) && (methodSpecs.size() >= maxMethods) )
213            {
214                addSuppressableWarning( CLASS_WITH_TOO_MANY_METHODS );
215            }
216
217            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
218            return this;
219        }   //  addMethod()
220
221        /**
222         *  {@inheritDoc}
223         */
224        @Override
225        @SuppressWarnings( "CastToConcreteClass" )
226        public final Builder addProperty( final FieldSpec fieldSpec, final boolean readOnly )
227        {
228            final var fieldSpecImpl = (FieldSpecImpl) requireValidNonNullArgument( fieldSpec, "fieldSpec", v -> v.hasModifier( PRIVATE ), $ -> format( "Field %s needs to be private", fieldSpec.name() ) );
229            addField( fieldSpecImpl );
230
231            final var fieldName = fieldSpecImpl.name();
232            final var propertyName = fieldName.startsWith( "m_" ) ? fieldName.substring( 2 ) : capitalize( fieldName );
233
234            final Set<Modifier> modifiers = EnumSet.of( PUBLIC, FINAL );
235            if( fieldSpec.hasModifier( STATIC ) ) modifiers.add( STATIC );
236
237            final var getter = getFactory().methodBuilder( "get" + propertyName )
238                .addModifiers( modifiers )
239                .returns( fieldSpecImpl.type() )
240                .addStatement( "return $N", fieldSpecImpl )
241                .build();
242            addMethod( getter );
243
244            if( !(readOnly || fieldSpecImpl.hasModifier( FINAL )) )
245            {
246                final var param = getFactory().parameterBuilder( fieldSpecImpl.type(), "value", FINAL )
247                    .build();
248                final var setter = getFactory().methodBuilder( "set" + propertyName )
249                    .addModifiers( modifiers )
250                    .addParameter( param )
251                    .returns( VOID_PRIMITIVE )
252                    .addStatement( "$N = $N", fieldSpecImpl, param )
253                    .build();
254                addMethod( setter );
255            }
256
257            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
258            return this;
259        }   //  addProperty()
260
261        /**
262         *  {@inheritDoc}
263         */
264        @Override
265        @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" )
266        public final RecordSpecImpl build()
267        {
268            checkState( getFieldSpecs().stream().anyMatch( fs -> !fs.hasModifier( STATIC ) ), () -> new IllegalStateException( "records without fields are not allowed" ) );
269
270            final var retValue = new RecordSpecImpl( this );
271
272            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
273            return retValue;
274        }   //  build()
275
276        /**
277         *  {@inheritDoc}
278         */
279        @Override
280        @SuppressWarnings( "CastToConcreteClass" )
281        public final BuilderImpl superclass( final TypeName superclass )
282        {
283            throw new IllegalStateException( format( "only classes have super classes, not " + RECORD ) );
284        }   //  superclass()
285    }

317    /**

319     */

321    protected final TypeSpecImpl createCopy() { return new RecordSpecImpl( this ); }
322
323    /**
324     *  Emits the type to the given code writer, using the layout as defined
325     *  by the Foundation library code.
326     *
327     *  @param  codeWriter  The target code writer.
328     *  @param  enumName    The name of the enum; can be {@code null}.
329     *  @param  implicitModifiers   The implicit modifiers.
330     *  @throws UncheckedIOException A problem occurred when writing to the
331     *      output target.
332     */
333    @SuppressWarnings( {"BoundedWildcard", "OptionalGetWithoutIsPresent", "CastToConcreteClass"} )
334    protected final void emit4Foundation( final CodeWriter codeWriter, final String enumName, final Set<Modifier> implicitModifiers ) throws UncheckedIOException
335    {
336        /*
337         * Push an empty type (specifically without nested types) for
338         * type-resolution.
339         */
340        codeWriter.pushType( createCopy() );
341
342        var javadoc = (CodeBlockImpl) getJavadoc();
343        var needSuppressWarningJavadoc = javadoc.isEmpty();
344
345        //--* Non-static fields *----------------------------------------------
346        final Collection<ParameterSpecImpl> nonStaticFields = new ArrayList<>();
347        for( final var fieldSpec : getFieldSpecs() )
348        {
349            if( fieldSpec.hasModifier( STATIC ) ) continue;
350            final var paramSpec = (ParameterSpecImpl) getFactory().parameterBuilder( fieldSpec.type(), fieldSpec.name() )
351                .build();
352            nonStaticFields.add( paramSpec );
353            final var fieldJavaDoc = fieldSpec.getJavadoc();
354            if( fieldJavaDoc.isEmpty() )
355            {
356                needSuppressWarningJavadoc = true;
357            }
358            else
359            {
360                final var codeBlock = (CodeBlockImpl) getFactory().codeBlockOf( "@param $N", fieldSpec )
361                    .join( " ", fieldJavaDoc );
362                javadoc = (CodeBlockImpl) javadoc.join( "\n", codeBlock );
363            }
364        }
365
366        needSuppressWarningJavadoc &= !javadoc.isEmpty() ;
367        codeWriter.emitJavadoc( javadoc );
368
369        final Set<SuppressableWarnings> suppressableWarnings = EnumSet.copyOf( getSuppressableWarnings() );
370        if( needSuppressWarningJavadoc ) suppressableWarnings.add( JAVADOC );
371        final Collection<AnnotationSpecImpl> annotations = new ArrayList<>( getAnnotations() );
372        getFactory().createSuppressWarningsAnnotation( suppressableWarnings )
373            .map( a -> (AnnotationSpecImpl) a )
374            .ifPresent( annotations::add );
375        codeWriter.emitAnnotations( annotations, false );
376        codeWriter.emitModifiers( modifiers(), union( implicitModifiers, RECORD.asMemberModifiers() ) );
377        codeWriter.emit( "$1L $2L", RECORD.name().toLowerCase( ROOT ), name().get() );
378        codeWriter.emitTypeVariables( getTypeVariables() );
379
380        var firstMember = true;
381        for( final var paramSpec : nonStaticFields )
382        {
383            codeWriter.emit( firstMember ? "( " : ", " );
384            paramSpec.emit( codeWriter, false );
385            firstMember = false;
386        }
387        codeWriter.emit( " )" );
388
389        //---* The implemented interfaces *------------------------------------
390        final var implementsTypes = getSuperInterfaces();
391        if( !implementsTypes.isEmpty() )
392        {
393            codeWriter.emit( " implements" );
394            var firstType = true;
395            for( final var type : implementsTypes )
396            {
397                if( !firstType ) codeWriter.emit( "," );
398                codeWriter.emit( " $T", type );
399                firstType = false;
400            }
401        }
402
403        codeWriter.popType();
404
405        //---* Get the static fields *-----------------------------------------
406        final var staticFields = getFieldSpecs().stream()
407            .filter( fs -> fs.hasModifier( STATIC ) )
408            .toList();
409
410        if( staticFields.isEmpty() && getStaticBlock().isEmpty() && getInitializerBlock().isEmpty() && getMethodSpecs().isEmpty() )
411        {
412            //---* We do not have a body for the record … *--------------------
413            codeWriter.emit( " { /* Empty */ " );
414        }
415        else
416        {
417            codeWriter.pushType( this );
418
419            codeWriter.emit(
420                """
421                \n{
422                """ );
423
424            //---* Emit the class body *---------------------------------------
425            codeWriter.indent();
426            firstMember = true;
427
428            //---* Emit the inner types *--------------------------------------
429            if( !innerClasses().isEmpty() )
430            {
431                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
432                codeWriter.emit(
433                    """
434                        /*---------------*\\
435                    ====** Inner Classes **====================================================
436                        \\*---------------*/""" );
437                innerClasses().stream()
438                    .sorted( comparing( t -> t.name().get(), CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER ) )
439                    .map( t -> (TypeSpecImpl) t)
440                    .forEachOrdered( t ->
441                    {
442                        codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
443                        t.emit( codeWriter, null, RECORD.implicitTypeModifiers() );
444                    } );
445                firstMember = false;
446            }
447
448            //--- Constants and attributes *-----------------------------------
449            if( !staticFields.isEmpty() )
450            {
451                final Collection<FieldSpecImpl> alreadyHandled = new HashSet<>();
452
453                //---* Emit the constants *----------------------------------------
454                final var constants = staticFields.stream()
455                    .filter( f -> f.hasModifier( PUBLIC ) )
456                    .filter( f -> f.hasModifier( FINAL ) )
457                    .filter( FieldSpecImpl::hasInitializer )
458                    .sorted( comparing( FieldSpecImpl::name, CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER ) )
459                    .toList();
460
461                if( !constants.isEmpty() )
462                {
463                    if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
464                    codeWriter.emit(
465                        """    
466                            /*-----------*\\
467                        ====** Constants **========================================================
468                            \\*-----------*/""" );
469                    constants.forEach( c ->
470                    {
471                        codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
472                        c.emit( codeWriter, RECORD.implicitFieldModifiers() );
473                        alreadyHandled.add( c );
474                    } );
475                    firstMember = false;
476                }
477
478                //---* Static fields *-----------------------------------------
479                final var statics = getFieldSpecs().stream()
480                    .filter( f -> !alreadyHandled.contains( f ) )
481                    .sorted( comparing( FieldSpecImpl::name, CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER ) )
482                    .toList();
483                if( !statics.isEmpty() || !getStaticBlock().isEmpty() )
484                {
485                    if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
486                    codeWriter.emit(
487                        """
488                            /*------------------------*\\
489                        ====** Static Initialisations **===========================================
490                            \\*------------------------*/""" );
491
492                    statics.forEach( s ->
493                    {
494                        codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
495                        s.emit( codeWriter, RECORD.implicitFieldModifiers() );
496                        alreadyHandled.add( s );
497                    } );
498
499                    //---* Static Block *--------------------------------------
500                    if( !getStaticBlock().isEmpty() )
501                    {
502                        codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
503                        codeWriter.emit( getStaticBlock() );
504                    }
505                    firstMember = false;
506                }
507            }
508
509            //---* Constructors *----------------------------------------------
510            final var constructors = getMethodSpecs().stream()
511                .filter( MethodSpecImpl::isConstructor )
512                .sorted( comparing( MethodSpecImpl::toString, CASE_INSENSITIVE_ORDER ) )
513                .toList();
514            if( !getInitializerBlock().isEmpty() || !constructors.isEmpty() )
515            {
516                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
517                codeWriter.emit(
518                    """
519                        /*--------------*\\
520                    ====** Constructors **=====================================================
521                        \\*--------------*/""" );
522
523                //---* Initializer block *-------------------------------------
524                if( !getInitializerBlock().isEmpty() )
525                {
526                    codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
527                    codeWriter.emit( getInitializerBlock() );
528                }
529
530                //---* Emit the constructors *---------------------------------
531                constructors.forEach( c ->
532                {
533                    codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
534                    c.emit( codeWriter, name(), RECORD.implicitMethodModifiers() );
535                } );
536                firstMember = false;
537            }
538
539            //---* Methods (static and non-static) *---------------------------
540            final var methods = getMethodSpecs().stream()
541                .filter( m -> !m.isConstructor() )
542                .sorted( TypeSpecImpl::compareMethodSpecs )
543                .toList();
544            if( !methods.isEmpty() )
545            {
546                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
547                codeWriter.emit(
548                    """
549                        /*---------*\\
550                    ====** Methods **==========================================================
551                        \\*---------*/""" );
552
553                methods.forEach( m ->
554                {
555                    codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
556                    m.emit( codeWriter, name(), RECORD.implicitMethodModifiers() );
557                } );
558            }
559
560            codeWriter.unindent();
561            codeWriter.popType();
562        }
563
564        codeWriter.emit(
565            """
566            }
567            //  $L $N
568            """, RECORD.name().toLowerCase( ROOT ), this );
569    }   //  emit4Foundation()
570
571    /**
572     *  Emits the type to the given code writer, using the layout as defined
573     *  by the original JavaPoet code.
574     *
575     *  @param  codeWriter  The target code writer.
576     *  @param  enumName    The name of the enum; can be {@code null}.
577     *  @param  implicitModifiers   The implicit modifiers.
578     *  @throws UncheckedIOException A problem occurred when writing to the
579     *      output target.
580     */
581    @SuppressWarnings( {"BoundedWildcard", "OptionalGetWithoutIsPresent", "CastToConcreteClass"} )
582    protected final void emit4JavaPoet( final CodeWriter codeWriter, final String enumName, final Set<Modifier> implicitModifiers ) throws UncheckedIOException
583    {
584        /*
585         * Push an empty type (specifically without nested types) for
586         * type-resolution.
587         */
588        codeWriter.pushType( createCopy() );
589
590        var javadoc = getJavadoc();
591
592        //--* Non-static fields *----------------------------------------------
593        final Collection<ParameterSpecImpl> nonStaticFields = new ArrayList<>();
594        for( final var fieldSpec : getFieldSpecs() )
595        {
596            if( fieldSpec.hasModifier( STATIC ) ) continue;
597            final var paramSpec = (ParameterSpecImpl) getFactory().parameterBuilder( fieldSpec.type(), fieldSpec.name() )
598                .build();
599            nonStaticFields.add( paramSpec );
600            final var fieldJavaDoc = fieldSpec.getJavadoc();
601            if( !fieldJavaDoc.isEmpty() )
602            {
603                final var codeBlock = (CodeBlockImpl) getFactory().codeBlockOf( "@param $N", fieldSpec )
604                    .join( " ", fieldJavaDoc );
605                javadoc = (CodeBlockImpl) javadoc.join( "\n", codeBlock );
606            }
607        }
608
609        codeWriter.emitJavadoc( javadoc );
610        final Collection<AnnotationSpecImpl> annotations = new ArrayList<>( getAnnotations() );
611        getFactory().createSuppressWarningsAnnotation( getSuppressableWarnings() )
612            .map( a -> (AnnotationSpecImpl) a )
613            .ifPresent( annotations::add );
614        codeWriter.emitAnnotations( annotations, false );
615        codeWriter.emitModifiers( modifiers(), union( implicitModifiers, RECORD.asMemberModifiers() ) );
616        codeWriter.emit( "$1L $2L", RECORD.name().toLowerCase( ROOT ), name().get() );
617        codeWriter.emitTypeVariables( getTypeVariables() );
618
619        var firstMember = true;
620        for( final var paramSpec : nonStaticFields )
621        {
622            codeWriter.emit( firstMember ? "(" : ", " );
623            paramSpec.emit( codeWriter, false );
624            firstMember = false;
625        }
626        codeWriter.emit( ")" );
627
628        //---* The implemented interfaces *------------------------------------
629        final var implementsTypes = getSuperInterfaces();
630        if( !implementsTypes.isEmpty() )
631        {
632            codeWriter.emit( " implements" );
633            var firstType = true;
634            for( final var type : implementsTypes )
635            {
636                if( !firstType ) codeWriter.emit( "," );
637                codeWriter.emit( " $T", type );
638                firstType = false;
639            }
640        }
641
642        codeWriter.popType();
643
644        //---* Get the static fields *-----------------------------------------
645        final var staticFields = getFieldSpecs().stream()
646            .filter( fs -> fs.hasModifier( STATIC ) )
647            .toList();
648
649        if( staticFields.isEmpty() && getStaticBlock().isEmpty() && getInitializerBlock().isEmpty() && getMethodSpecs().isEmpty() )
650        {
651            //---* We do not have a body for the record … *--------------------
652            codeWriter.emit( " {}\n" );
653        }
654        else
655        {
656            codeWriter.pushType( this );
657
658            //---* Emit the record body *--------------------------------------
659            codeWriter.emit( " {\n" );
660
661            codeWriter.indent();
662
663            //---* Static fields *---------------------------------------------
664            firstMember = true;
665            for( final var fieldSpec : staticFields )
666            {
667                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
668                fieldSpec.emit( codeWriter, EnumSet.noneOf( Modifier.class ) );
669                firstMember = false;
670            }
671
672            if( !getStaticBlock().isEmpty() )
673            {
674                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
675                codeWriter.emit( getStaticBlock() );
676                firstMember = false;
677            }
678
679            //---* Initializer block *-----------------------------------------
680            if( !getInitializerBlock().isEmpty() )
681            {
682                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
683                codeWriter.emit( getInitializerBlock() );
684                firstMember = false;
685            }
686
687            //---* Constructors *----------------------------------------------
688            for( final var methodSpec : getMethodSpecs() )
689            {
690                if( !methodSpec.isConstructor() ) continue;
691                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
692                methodSpec.emit( codeWriter, name(), RECORD.implicitMethodModifiers() );
693                firstMember = false;
694            }
695
696            //---* Methods (static and non-static) *---------------------------
697            for( final var methodSpec : getMethodSpecs() )
698            {
699                if( methodSpec.isConstructor() ) continue;
700                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
701                methodSpec.emit( codeWriter, name(), RECORD.implicitMethodModifiers() );
702                firstMember = false;
703            }
704
705            //---* Types (inner classes) *-------------------------------------
706            for( final var typeSpec : innerClasses() )
707            {
708                if( !firstMember ) codeWriter.emit( "\n" );
709                ((TypeSpecImpl) typeSpec).emit( codeWriter, null, RECORD.implicitTypeModifiers() );
710                firstMember = false;
711            }
712
713            codeWriter.unindent();
714            codeWriter.emit( "}\n" );
715            codeWriter.popType();
716        }
717    }   //  emit4JavaPoet()
718
719    /**
720     *  {@inheritDoc}
721     */
722    @Override
723    public final boolean equals( final Object o )
724    {
725        var retValue = this == o;
726        if( !retValue && (o instanceof RecordSpecImpl other) )
727        {
728            retValue = getFactory().equals( other.getFactory() ) && toString().equals( o.toString() );
729        }
730
731        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
732        return retValue;
733    }   //  equals()

736     *  {@inheritDoc}
737     */

741    /**
742     *  {@inheritDoc}
743     */
744    @SuppressWarnings( {"CastToConcreteClass", "OptionalGetWithoutIsPresent"} )
745    @Override
746    public final TypeSpecImpl.BuilderImpl toBuilder()
747    {
748        final var retValue = new BuilderImpl( getFactory(), name().get() );
749        retValue.getJavadoc().addWithoutDebugInfo( getJavadoc() );
750        retValue.getAnnotations().addAll( getAnnotations() );
751        retValue.getModifiers().addAll( modifiers() );
752        retValue.getTypeVariables().addAll( getTypeVariables() );
753        retValue.superclass( getSuperClass() );
754        retValue.getSuperinterfaces().addAll( getSuperInterfaces() );
755        retValue.getFieldSpecs().addAll( getFieldSpecs() );
756        retValue.getMethodSpecs().addAll( getMethodSpecs() );
757        retValue.getTypeSpecs().addAll( typeSpecs() );
758        retValue.getInitializerBlock().addWithoutDebugInfo( getInitializerBlock() );
759        retValue.getStaticBlock().addWithoutDebugInfo( getStaticBlock() );
760        retValue.getStaticImports().addAll( getStaticImports() );
761        retValue.addSuppressableWarning( getSuppressableWarnings().toArray( SuppressableWarnings[]::new ) );
762
763        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
764        return retValue;
765    }   //  toBuilder()
